  "text": "Mice. AR lox mice were generated as described previously [CITATION_1] , and targeted AR lox offspring were backcrossed onto a C57BL/6 background for more than six generations. ␣-Actin cre mice [CITATION_2] and muscle creatine kinase (MCK)-cre mice (2), used in matings to generate the AR lox and wild-type males examined in this study, were also backcrossed onto a C57BL/6 background for more than six generations before use. Southern and PCR analysis of the targeted locus confirmed that no gene rearrangement or alternate splicing products are produced from the AR lox locus (Ref. [CITATION_3] and data not shown). Wild-type males were littermates of AR lox males. Mice were housed in a conventional facility, with standard chow and water available ad libitum. All mouse studies were performed with the approval of the Austin Health Animal Ethics Committee.",
